<<> AzureBlade: Wait for me! I am coming to meet you!
> 
> He blasts full speed towards the spark.>>

Mistra lined up carefully with the status pod, so as to push it by her 
shoulder. Hopefully she was big enough...her stature was small and light when 
it came down to it. Taking in a deep breath, she charged foward to push with 
all her weight...

...and was nursing a throbbing shoulder a moment later, after tumbling 
backwards a few feet. Muttering some words under her breath that are better 
off not repeated, she moved foward again, pushing in place with her shoulder. 

Seeing soon this wasn't getting her anywhere, since the pod hadn't budged in 
the least, Mistra sighed and sat down beside it, glaring in its general 
direction. Great. Just great. 

"If I just knew my activation code...then I could transform and move this 
damn thing no problem. I think anyway.." Not that she could remember just 
what her actual form looked like. For all she knew, she maybe just as small...

Snarling slightly in annoyance, she kicked a small stone towards the pod, 
then looked out towards the sky. Maybe she should just forget the status pod 
and move on...why would anyone want to steal it anyway? There may not even be 
another soul on this planet...even if there was, what use would her pod be to 
them? But..then again...

--part1_ad.17c16785.2991d4c9_boundary
